Quote:  "Major Kemp, although actually a Government officer, seems," stated "The Post," "to have been acting in a very turbulent and violent manner, interfering with the surveys and demolishing trigonometrical stations, because he had a difference of opinion with some other Natives as to the manner in which the block should be surveyed," but "the whole affair appears a very trumpery one, and not of sufficient importance to create the slightest anxiety.["]
